.TH "dprc_get_connection" 9 "dprc_get_connection" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
dprc_get_connection \- Get connected endpoint and link status if connection exists.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" dprc_get_connection
.BI "(struct fsl_mc_io *mc_io "  ","
.BI "u32 cmd_flags "  ","
.BI "u16 token "  ","
.BI "const struct dprc_endpoint *endpoint1 "  ","
.BI "struct dprc_endpoint *endpoint2 "  ","
.BI "int *state "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "mc_io" 12
Pointer to MC portal's I/O object
.IP "cmd_flags" 12
Command flags; one or more of 'MC_CMD_FLAG_'
.IP "token" 12
Token of DPRC object
.IP "endpoint1" 12
Endpoint 1 configuration parameters
.IP "endpoint2" 12
Returned endpoint 2 configuration parameters
.IP "state" 12
Returned link state:
1 - link is up;
0 - link is down;
-1 - no connection (endpoint2 information is irrelevant)
.SH "RETURN"
'0' on Success; -ENOTCONN if connection does not exist.
